HEN wounded sore the stricken soul Lies bleeding and unbound‚ One only Hand, a pierced Hand, Can salve the sinuer's wound.

When sorrow swells the laden breast, And tears of anguish flow,

One only Heart, a broken Heart, Can feel the sinner’s woe.

When penitence has wept in vain Over some foul dark spot,

One only stream, a stream of blood, Can wash away the blot.

’Tis Jesus’ Blood that washes white, His Hand that brings relief3 ‚ His Heart is touched with all our joys„ And feeleth for our grief.

Lift up Thy bleeding Hand, O Lord, Unseal that cleansing tide ; We have no shelter from our sin But in Thy wounded side. —Frances Cecil Alexander.
